Package wireframe

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Groupable
    A Groupable consists of something on a Wireframe that can be grouped together.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractElement
    The AbstractElement class provides some of the basic implementation shared by its subclasses Annotation and AbstractWireframeElement.
    AbstractWireframeElement
    A wireframe element this, simply, not an Annotation.
    Annotation
    A wireframe element that can be attached to another element for the purpose of displaying useful information about that element.
    ComboBox
    A ComboBox element is a box in a wireframe that holds multiple options that can be selected.
    Enums
    The Enums class holds the enums that the Wireframe package uses.
    Group
    A Group links together a list of elements so that modifications to one element of the group also apply to other elements of the group.
    Header
    A Header element represents some blocked-out text that is larger than regular text, meant as a headline.
    Image
    An Image element represents a picture on a wireframe.
    ListElement
    A ListElement element represents a blocked-out text list in a wireframe.
    Location
    A Location object is simply a wrapper for a x value and a y value.
    Paragraph
    A Paragraph element represents a blocked-out block of text in a wireframe.
    ProgressBar
    A ProgressBar element represents a horizontal progress bar in a wireframe (like a loading bar).
    RoundedBox
    A RoundedBox element is just a box with rounded edges in a wireframe.
    ScrollBar
    A ScrollBar element represents a vertical progress bar in a wireframe (like a sidebar).
    Slider
    A Slider element represents a horizontal slider in a wireframe.
    Text
    A Text element represents a block of canned text in a wireframe.
    Wireframe
    The Wireframe class is the outermost interface of the wireframe package.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Enums.Alignment
    The Alignment enum is used to designate the alignment of text or blocked text for a wireframe element
    Enums.ElementType
    The ElementType enum designates types of wireframe elements.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    LockedException
    A LockedException is an exception meant to be thrown whenever a method attempted to illegally modify an object that was locked.
    WireframeException
    A WireframeException is a general exception type that can be thrown by classes in the Wireframe package.
